                "head": {
                    "value": "Historical/Biographical Note"
                },
                "p": [
                    {
                        "value": "Marvin Markman (d. 2002) was a Communist Party member, and was also the Executive Vice President of Advance, a radical youth organization. Markman later became a public school teacher in New York City and a leader of the Party's rank and file activism in the United Federation of Teachers, via the Teachers Action Caucus, and in the American Federation of Teachers, via the United Action Caucus."
                    }
                ]
            }
        ],
